<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-671-100  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 671 100.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  July 23 1990 v12 n30 p30(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>True Type's operations transparent to end-users. (Apple MacintoshSystem 7.0 font technology)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Coale, Kristi.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The True Type rasterizing software in System 7.0 for the Macintoshconsumes only about 50Kbytes of memory.andP;  It can be used withapplications that have not been rewritten, since its operationswill be transparent to applications.andP;  A font and size are selectedby users in their applications and the resource data is sent tothe Font Manager, which translates the information to make anoutline.andP;  The font definition is scaled to a specific point sizeand adjusted by the font manager to work with the display devicebefore it is made into a bit map.andP;  The final result is a smoothfont on both the page and the screen.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Apple Computer Inc. (products).andO;Ticker:    AAPL.andO;Product:   True Type (Printer software) (design and construction).andO;Topic:     PrintersSoftware PackagesFonts.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>